  <h2 style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;"> I Describe myself as a provocateur</h2><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="sqsrte-large">Or an alien, some people have said that about me too. I’m a person that loves to invoke spontaneity out of others. I find when people are present, they are their fullest self. People live solitary lives in their head because it is easy. Acting pulls us out of that grey cage. I want to bring chaos, love, and violence to people’s lives… In an art form, of course.</p><p style="text-align:center;margin-left:40px;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="sqsrte-large">I find inspiration in classics, puppetry, and physical theater. I paint self-portraits when I’m inspired (depressed). I take aesthetic videos smoking Virginia Slims so that I can say I have a social media presence. I love to teach and play <a href="https://www.chess.com/home">chess</a> and when I have the time, play a melodramatic bard in DnD. </p><p style="text-align:center;white-space:pre-wrap;" class="sqsrte-large">Stoic has been a word used to define how I represent myself. &nbsp;It's small talk. I don't really enjoy it. It doesn’t get us anywhere besides learning it was hot earlier today. I want stories, facts, feelings, opinions, and nonsensical drama with everyone I meet. Give it all to me and let me live in it. I want to relish life outside the mundanity with acting. </p>
</div>




















  
  



</div></div></div></div></div>
